transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra. This is Charles.

Speaker 2: Hi there. How are you?

Speaker 1: Doing good. How about yourself?

Speaker 2: Good. Let me get you off the speaker there.

Speaker 1: Hey, I have an account with you guys, and I ordered with ScoreBlue,

Speaker 2: and I ordered one prescription, and I'm dissatisfied with it,

Speaker 1: so I want to make sure that you guys don't send me any more.

Speaker 2: Understood. I got John Powers in Rockwall, Texas?

Speaker 1: That is correct.

Speaker 2: Okay. Were the pills just not effective?

Speaker 1: Did they give you side effects, or what happened with it?

Speaker 2: No, they were – it's just Sildenafil.

Speaker 1: I've been using Sildenafil for several years.

Speaker 2: I was under the impression this was something different,

Speaker 1: and it's the same product, so it doesn't work for me any better

Speaker 2: or any worse than what I've already been using,

Speaker 1: and I can get it for $10 from my HMO,

Speaker 2: so I don't need to spend $70 for it.

Speaker 1: I understand. So with our pills, our pills are FDA-approved with Pfizer, okay?

Speaker 2: So Sildenafil is an active ingredient in any Viagra.

Speaker 1: It doesn't matter where you get it from.

Speaker 2: Sildenafil is always going to be in it because it's an active ingredient.

Speaker 1: So you tried the pills, though?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: They didn't work any better or any worse for me than the others.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Especially on the 11-minute, you know, working in 11 minutes kind of thing.

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: That didn't happen.

Speaker 1: Right. Right. Okay.

Speaker 2: So, I mean, we are with Pfizer, John,

Speaker 1: so it's always disappointing when we hear that our product isn't taking its full effect like it should.

Speaker 2: So if need be, I mean, we are with Pfizer.

Speaker 1: Like I said, we do have another variation of the Viagra AGV made in our France factory.

Speaker 2: So if you'd like, I don't want to sell it to you.

Speaker 1: I want to make sure you have a pleasant experience with us and leave no stone unturned.

Speaker 2: I can send you a sample completely for free of 10 pills of the Viagra AGV that's made in our France factory.

Speaker 1: I can almost guarantee you're going to like this one a lot better.

Speaker 2: Anybody I send it to, they almost call back within a couple of weeks asking for a refill.

Speaker 1: So I can send it to you for free.

Speaker 2: Call me back at 0040.

Speaker 1: You won't have to hear that terrible elevator music anymore, and you'll just go directly to my queue,

Speaker 2: and then we'll talk about future accommodations for your future refills with the pill I send you.

Speaker 1: Well, what I'm trying to do right now, you guys, do you have these set up on an automatic refill?

Speaker 2: Negative.

Speaker 1: I'm going to pump the brakes on sending you anything for the next four or five months.

Speaker 2: That way you've got time to try the one that I send you, and then call me back.

Speaker 1: Let me know what the future deal is with the refills and when you need it, okay?

Speaker 2: Yeah, hold on.

Speaker 1: Don't go.

Speaker 2: You're not going, are you?

Speaker 1: No, no, no, no.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah.

Speaker 1: Let me just back up a little bit here.

Speaker 2: Did you guys have me on an automatic refill?

Speaker 1: On an automatic refill?

Speaker 2: It's a prescription refill, correct, yeah.

Speaker 1: So your next one wasn't due until it looks like March.

Speaker 2: Right.

Speaker 1: So I definitely want you to remove me from that and go ahead.

Speaker 2: I appreciate your offer, but I'm going to ask you to go ahead and close out my account

Speaker 1: and don't send me any refills, don't send me any samples, don't send me any products at all.

Speaker 2: Sounds good.

Speaker 1: All righty then.

Speaker 2: But I do appreciate your offer.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Sounds good.

Speaker 1: All right then, John.

Speaker 2: Hope you have a great day.

Speaker 1: Well, wait, wait.

Speaker 2: How do I know that you've canceled my account?

Speaker 1: I'll send you an email and you can also see it online.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Thank you very much, and I'll let the credit card company know as well.

Speaker 2: Hello?

Speaker 1: Let them know what?

Speaker 2: Not to accept any more bills from you guys.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay, okay.

Speaker 2: That happens sometimes where, you know, you're doing your job and then somebody drops the ball

Speaker 1: and then you wind up getting billed for another prescription or whatever that you didn't want.

Speaker 2: I always double down on this.

Speaker 1: Fair enough.

Speaker 2: But thank you very much.

Speaker 1: I do appreciate your time, and again, I do appreciate the offer.

Speaker 2: You seem like a very nice guy.

Speaker 1: But cancel everything, and I'll look forward to getting that email.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Sounds good.

Speaker 2: Hope you have a great day, John.

Speaker 1: Take care.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: You too.
